ENTRY       EC 5.5.1.16                 Enzyme
NAME        halimadienyl-diphosphate synthase;
            Rv3377c;
            halimadienyl diphosphate synthase;
            tuberculosinol diphosphate synthase;
            halima-5(6),13-dien-15-yl-diphosphate lyase (cyclizing)
CLASS       Isomerases;
            Intramolecular lyases;
            Intramolecular lyases (only sub-subclass identified to date)
SYSNAME     halima-5,13-dien-15-yl-diphosphate lyase (decyclizing)
REACTION    geranylgeranyl diphosphate = tuberculosinyl diphosphate [RN:R09715]
ALL_REAC    R09715
SUBSTRATE   geranylgeranyl diphosphate [CPD:C00353]
PRODUCT     tuberculosinyl diphosphate [CPD:C19836]
COMMENT     Requires Mg2+ for activity. This enzyme is found in pathogenic prokaryotes such as Mycobacterium tuberculosis but not in non-pathogens such as Mycobacterium smegmatis so may play a role in pathogenicity. The product of the reaction is subsequently dephosphorylated yielding tuberculosinol (halima-5,13-dien-15-ol).
